20a%2031-year-old%20HR%20director%20in%20New%20Jersey.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhr-leaders-recruiters-hiring-managers-manage-stress-burnout-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworked%20in%20HR%20%3C%2Fa%3Efor%2010%20years%2C%20specifically%2C%20I%20work%20with%20senior%20leaders%20to%20ensure%20all%20sorts%20of%20HR%20compliance%20is%20in%20place.%20I%20do%20it%20all%20from%20coaching%20leaders%2C%20driving%20engagement%2C%20boosting%20team%20morale%2C%20and%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20HR%2C%20people%20are%20usually%20curious%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftips-stand-out-candidates-applicants-job-market-recruiter-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehow%20to%20stand%20out%20at%20work%3C%2Fa%3E.%20To%20that%2C%20I'd%20say%2C%20go%20above%20and%20beyond%2C%20find%20ways%20to%20be%20innovative%2C%20and%20come%20to%20the%20table%20with%20solutions%2C%20not%20just%20problems.%20But%20beyond%20what%20you%20should%20do%2C%20there%20are%20also%20things%20you%20shouldn't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20working%20in%20HR%20for%2010%20years%2C%20here%20are%20three%20things%20I'd%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fways-youre-annoying-coworkers-2017-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enever%20do%20in%20the%20workplace%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20Don't%20overshare%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20point%20I%20preach%20is%20not%20to%20overshare%20at%20work.%20It's%20easy%20to%20become%20comfortable%20with%20your%20colleagues.%20After%20all%2C%20you%20spend%20eight%20hours%20a%20day%20with%20them%2C%20if%20not%20more.%20Even%20for%20remote%20workers%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20role%2C%20there's%20still%20a%20significant%20connection%20to%20coworkers%2C%20but%20it's%20important%20to%20remember%20they%20aren't%20your%20automatic%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsharing-at-work-stop-oversharing-in-office-professional-growth-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOversharing%20at%20work%20%3C%2Fa%3Eoften%20does%20more%20harm%20than%20good%20because%20it%20allows%20people%20to%20make%20assumptions%20or%20decisions%20for%20you%2C%20even%20if%20it%20does%20come%20from%20a%20caring%20place%2C%20it's%20not%20a%20good%20idea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20not%20thinking%20much%20of%20it%2C%20I%20once%20told%20a%20coworker%20about%20issues%20I%20was%20having%20with%20my%20car.%20Then%2C%20a%20couple%20of%20months%20later%2C%20an%20opportunity%20arose%20for%20me%20to%20move%20into%20a%20larger%20scope%20of%20work%2C%20requiring%20me%20to%20drive%20to%20different%20locations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20manager%20sat%20down%20with%20me%2C%20he%20mentioned%20he%20had%20heard%20about%20my%20car%20issues%20and%20expressed%20concern%20about%20me%20getting%20%26quot%3Bstuck.%26quot%3B%20As%20a%20result%2C%20the%20job%20opportunity%20wasn't%20given%20to%20me.%20I%20was%20so%20bummed%20out%2C%20and%20I%20felt%20burned.%20It%20made%20me%20realize%20I%20shouldn't%20share%20things%20in%20my%20personal%20life%20with%20those%20I%20work%20with%2C%20as%20it%20gives%20people%20the%20opportunity%20to%20weigh%20in%20and%20make%20decisions%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20Don't%20be%20humble%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20learned%20not%20to%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhumblebragging-could-impact-chances-of-promotion-career-workplace-experts-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etoo%20humble%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20workplace%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20don't%20mean%20anyone%20should%20be%20cocky%2C%20think%20they're%20better%20than%20everyone%20else%2C%20or%20be%20a%20jerk%3B%20that%20won't%20get%20you%20very%20far%2C%20either.%20I%20believe%20you%20can%20be%20kind%20and%20empathetic%2C%20but%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20you%20can't%20let%20people%20step%20all%20over%20you%20and%20you%20shouldn't%20put%20yourself%20last%20in%20comparison%20to%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20my%20HR%20role%2C%20I've%20noticed%2C%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftraits-of-highly-successful-individuals-ceos-millionaires-real-estate-investors-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esuccessful%20people%20tend%20to%20be%20very%20direct%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20their%20accomplishments%20and%20more%20vocal%2C%20whereas%20super-humble%20individuals%20tend%20not%20to%20talk%20about%20their%20achievements%20or%20advocate%20for%20themselves%20as%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20it's%20easier%20for%20them%20to%20get%20passed%20up%20for%20promotions%2C%20and%20for%20them%20to%20fade%20into%20the%20background.%20I%20myself%20was%20once%20a%20big%20believer%20that%20my%20work%20would%20speak%20for%20itself%2C%20but%20I've%20since%20learned%20that%20if%20you%20don't%20advocate%20for%20yourself%2C%20no%20one%20else%20will.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20Don't%20stick%20around%20too%20long%20at%20parties%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20someone%20who's%20worked%20in%20HR%2C%20I've%20played%20a%20role%20in%20organizing%20events%20where%20I've%20had%20to%20stay%20to%20the%20end%2C%20or%20just%20pop%20in%20when%20I%20can.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20I've%20seen%20more%20negative%20things%20come%20out%20of%20sticking%20around%20too%20long%20at%20company%20functions%20than%20positive%20ones.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbusiness-and-booze-happy-hour-etiquette-2011-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESometimes%2C%20it's%20the%20alcoho%3C%2Fa%3El%20%E2%80%94%20people%20will%20start%20drinking%2C%20and%20it%20just%20goes%20too%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20times%2C%20people%20will%20be%20very%20much%20sober%20but%20make%20poor%20decisions%20because%20they're%20around%20their%20coworkers%20but%20in%20a%20different%20setting%20than%20the%20office.%20When%20they%20come%20into%