%2C%20but%20they%20are%20collecting%20experiences.%20%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20have%20to%20pay%20for%20plane%20tickets%20or%20hotels%2C%20so%20we%20can%20experience%20more%20for%20our%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20Emily%20Scherrer%20said.%20So%20far%20they've%20taken%20the%20bus%20to%20Alaska%2C%20New%20Mexico%2C%20Texas%2C%20and%20Colorado.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20biggest%20expenses%20are%20car%20insurance%20(about%20%241%2C850%20a%20year)%2C%20diesel%20fuel%2C%20and%20satellite%20internet%20connection%2C%20which%20is%20%24150%20a%20month%20and%20is%20necessary%20for%20their%20jobs.%20Filling%20up%20the%20tank%20costs%20about%20%24300%3B%20on%20average%2C%20they%20fill%20up%20once%20or%20twice%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThey%20have%20ways%20to%20cut%20down%20on%20costs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20cost%20that's%20in%20their%20control%20is%20where%20they%20park.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20expenses%20depend%20on%20where%20we%20park%20and%20the%20amenities%20we%20find%2C%26quot%3B%20Emily%20Scherrer%20said.%20The%20southwestern%20US%20has%20a%20lot%20of%20land%20available%20for%20public%20use%2C%20such%20as%20BLM%20or%20Forest%20Service%20land%2C%20where%20parking%20for%20certain%20days%20is%20free.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20like%20to%20use%20that%20kind%20of%20land%20versus%20going%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftravel%2Fbest-us-campsites%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecampgrounds%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20saves%20us%20a%20lot%20of%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20also%20pay%20to%20fill%20up%20and%20dump%20their%20tanks%2C%20usually%20as%20a%20campground%20fee.%20There's%20a%20toilet%20and%20a%20shower%20on%20the%20bus%2C%20and%20the%20septic%20tanks%20must%20be%20dumped%20roughly%20every%20two%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20bathroom%20on%20a%20bus%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65d4eb6ea610a9069d5a92f4%