C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20%E2%80%9Czero%20interest%20rate%20phenomena%2C%E2%80%9D%20continues%2C%20tech%20workers%20affected%20by%20mass%20layoffs%20are%20trying%20to%20get%20a%20break%20where%20they%20can.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EOne%20possibility%20is%20the%20coding%20rounds%20of%20the%20typical%20tech%20job%20interview%2C%20where%20candidates%20are%20prompted%20by%20interviewers%20to%20solve%20technical%20problems.%20These%20interviews%20are%20usually%20conducted%20by%20a%20hiring%20manager%20for%20a%20team%20or%20company%2C%20and%20problems%20proposed%20are%20often%20taken%20from%20or%20based%20on%20the%20LeetCode%20interview%20prep%20platform.%20So%2C%20job%20candidates%20can%20easily%20use%20something%20like%20ChatGPT%20to%20effectively%20cheat%20their%20way%20to%20fast%20solutions%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finterviewing.io%2Fblog%2Fhow-hard-is-it-to-cheat-with-chatgpt-in-technical-interviews%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Erecent%20experiment%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20conducted%20by%20interviewing.io%2C%20a%20popular%20platform%20for%20mock%20tech%20interviews%20and%20industry%20recruiting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20is%20it%20easy%20to%20use%20ChatGPT%20to%20ace%20a%20typical%20coding%20round%20of%20a%20tech%20interview%2C%20interviewing.io%20found%20in%20an%20experiment%20last%20month%2C%20based%20on%2037%20tech%20job%20interviews%2C%20that%20no%20interviewers%20could%20tell%20when%20a%20candidate%20had%20used%20ChatGPT%20to%20answer%20or%20solve%20proposed%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAline%20Lerner%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20interviewing.io%20who%20previously%20worked%20as%20a%20tech%20recruiter%20and%20earlier%20an%20engineer%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20people%20conducting%20tech%20interviews%20today%20have%20come%20to%20expect%20a%20type%20of%20%E2%80%9Cperfect%20answer%E2%80%9D%20from%20job%20candidates.%20That%20leads%20to%20answers%20provided%20by%20something%20like%20ChatGPT%2C%20which%20is%20trained%20on%20information%20scraped%20from%20the%20internet%2C%20including%20massive%20amounts%20of%20technical%20coding%20problems%20and%20solutions%20from%20LeetCode%2C%20%E2%80%9Cto%20sound%20normal.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNow%2C%20through%20no%20fault%20of%20their%20own%20really%2C%20an%20interviewer%20can%20be%20biased%20against%20the%20candidate%20that%20is%20actually%20solving%20the%20problem%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%E2%80%9D%20Lerner%20said%2C%20giving%20a%20less%20polished%20but%20more%20creative%20answer%20to%20a%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20no%20one%20was%20caught%20or%20even%20suspected%20of%20using%20ChatGPT%20during%20the%20interview%20process%2C%20interviewing.io%20did%20find%20that%20ChatGPT%20was%20much%20less%20likely%20to%20give%20correct%20answers%20to%20proposed%20interview%20problems%20the%20more%20unique%20they%20were.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20coding%20problems%20were%20taken%20verbatim%20from%20LeetCode%2C%20job%20candidates%20using%20ChatGPT%20solved%20correctly%2073%25%20of%20the%20time%2C%20interviewing.io%20found.%20When%20LeetCode%20problems%20were%20modified%20slightly%2C%20answers%20were%20still%20correct%2067%25%20percent%20of%20the%20time.%20When%20a%20problem%20was%20custom%2C%20however%2C%20ChatGPT%20answers%20were%20correct%20only%2025%25%20of%20the%20time.%20That%E2%80%99s%20far%20worse%20than%20how%20tech%20job%20candidates%20fare%20on%20their%20own.%20Relying%20on%20their%20own%20abilities%2C%20interviewing.io%20found%20that%20job%20candidates%20passed%20coding%20rounds%20of%20interviews%2053%25%20of%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20a%20rise%20in%20major%20tech%20companies%20using%20mostly%20internal%20generative%20AI%20tools%20to%20help%20engineers%20write%20and%20fix%20code%20more%20quickly%20(Meta%20uses%20a%20tool%20called%20Metamate%2C%20once%20called%20Code%20Compose%3B%20Google%20just%20renamed%20its%20tool%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-g