C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWalmart%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Famazon%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20facing%20an%20onslaught%20of%20legal%20trouble%20over%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalmart-workers-reveal-what-its-like-work-largest-retailer-2021-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econtroversial%20points-based%20attendance%20systems%3C%2Fa%3E%20both%20businesses%20use%20to%20track%20worker%20absences%20and%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20fire%20employees%2C%20according%20to%20lawyers%20who%20have%20filed%20lawsuits%20against%20the%20retail%20titans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20November%202022%2C%20one%20California-based%20law%20firm%2C%20West%20Coast%20Trial%20Lawyers%2C%20has%20filed%20three%20wrongful%20termination%20lawsuits%20against%20Walmart%20and%20four%20against%20Amazon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20lawsuits%2C%20fired%20workers%20accuse%20the%20companies%20of%20violating%20their%20employment%20rights%20by%20terminating%20them%20after%20they%20took%20legally%20protected%20time%20for%20sick%2C%20medical%20or%20pregnancy-related%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20those%20cases%2C%20some%20of%20which%20allege%20disability%20discrimination%20and%20retaliation%2C%20were%20borne%20from%20the%20points-based%20attendance%20systems%20that%20Walmart%20and%20Amazon%20use%20%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20surge%20of%20similar%20complaints%20from%20fired%20workers%20have%20continued%20to%20roll%20in%20in%20recent%20months%2C%20attorneys%20with%20West%20Coast%20Trial%20Lawyers%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20the%20larger%20employers%20like%20Walmart%20and%20Amazon%20have%20started%20to%20use%20this%20points%20system%20with%20regards%20to%20absences%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20lawyer%20Ron%20Zambrano%2C%20the%20firm's%20Employment%20Litigation%20Chair.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZambrano%20is%20also%20suing%20rappers%20Lizzo%20and%20Ye%2C%20formerly%20known%20as%20Kanye%20West%2C%20on%20behalf%20of%20former%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EEmployees%20can%20be%20fired%20if%20they%20rack%20up%20enough%20points%20in%20a%20certain%20time%20frame%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20both%20Amazon%20and%20Walmart's%20points-based%20attendance%20policies%2C%20workers%20can%20be%20terminated%20once%20they%20rack%20up%20a%20certain%20amount%20of%20points%20in%20a%20specific%20time%20period%2C%20according%20to%20Zambrano%20and%20fellow%20attorney%20with%20West%20Coast%20Trial%20Lawyers%2C%20Nick%20Yasman.%20Being%20late%20or%20leaving%20early%20can%20cost%20an%20employee%20a%20fraction%20of%20a%20point%2C%20the%20attorneys%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWalmart%20would%20not%20provide%20details%20on%20its%20points-based%20attendance%20system%20to%20Business%20Insider.%20However%2C%20in%20a%202023%20deposition%20stemming%20from%20one%20of%20the%20wrongful%20termination%20lawsuits%20against%20the%20company%2C%20a%20%26quot%3Bpeople%20lead%26quot%3B%20or%20HR%20rep%20for%20the%20retail%20giant%20said%20Walmart%20uses%20a%20five-point%20system%20and%20noted%20that%20employees%20can%20be%20subject%20to%20termination%20if%20they%20accrue%20five%20points%20in%20a%20rolling%20six-month%20period%2C%20according%20to%20Yasman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKelly%20Hellbusch%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20Walmart%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20the%20company%20%26quot%3Boffers%20full-and%20part-time%20associates%20paid%20time%20off%20and%20protected%20paid%20time%20off%20to%20use%20for%20just%20about%20anything%20including%20when%20they%20are%20sick%20and%20miss%20work%20as%20well%20as%20accommodations%20and%20leave%20of%20absence%20options.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20a%20trusted%20and%20experienced%20employer%2C%20we%20have%20knowledgeable%20people%20partners%2C%20helpful%20resources%20and%20tools%20for%20associates%20and%20effective%20processes%20in%20place%20to%20comply%20with%20laws%20as%20well%20as%20our%20own%20policies%2C%26quot%3B%20Hellbusch%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225129%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20customer%20loading%20shopping%20into%20the%20back%20of%20a%20car%20in%20the%20parking%20lot%20of%20a%20Walmart%20store%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659efcbedcdb354a98567307%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223419%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWalmart%20is%20accused%20of%20violating%20the%20rights%20of%20employees%20who%20were%20fired%20for%20taking%20time%20off.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FJulio%20Cortez%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20the%20three%20recent%20wrongful%20termination%20lawsuits%20West%20Coast%20Trial%20Lawyers%20has%20filed%20against%20Walmart%2C%20Hellbusch%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20will%20continue%20to%20defend%20the%20company%20against%20this%20litigation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilar%20to%20Walmart's%20policy%2C%20Amazon%20uses%20a%20points-based%20attendance%20system%20that%20could%20land%20employees%20in%20hot%20water%20if%20they%20hit%20eight%20points%20in%20a%20rolling%2060-day%20period%2C%20according%20to%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20managers%20are%20alerted%20if%20workers%20accumulate%20eight%20points%20in%20a%20rolling%2060-day%20period%20and%20are%20%26quot%3Brequired%26quot%3B%20to%20reach%20out%20to%20their%20employees%20%26quot%3Bto%20better%20understand%20the%20situation.%26quot%3B%20Amazon%20would%20not%20clarify%20whether%20an%20employee%20hitting%20eight%20points%20would%20be%20grounds%20for%20termination.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESam%20Stephenson%2C%20an%20Amazon%20spokesperson%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felizabeth-warren-bernie-sanders-aoc-amazon-absence-policy-investigation-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompany's%20points-based%20attendance%20policy%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20used%20%26quot%3Bmostly%26quot%3B%20for%20part-time%20employees%20who%20work%20flexible%20schedules%20at%20the%20company's%20operations%20facilities.%20He%20said%20the%20policy%20is%20%26quot%3Benforced%20when%20an%20employee%20provides%20little%20to%20no%20notice%20for%20not%20showing%20up%20to%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Stephenson%2C%20the%20points%20system%20has%20human%20oversight%2C%20and%20the%20company%20works%20with%20its%20employees%20if%20they're%20dealing%20with%20an%20emergency%20or%20any%20unforeseen%20circumstances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20an%20employee%20has%20an%20unexpected%20scheduling%20issue%2C%20we%20work%20with%20them%20directly%20to%20provide%20options%20and%20solutions%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Stephenson%2C%20who%20added%20that%20employees%20have%20%26quot%3Boptions%20to%20use%20unpaid%20time%2C%20vacation%20time%2C%20and%20paid%20personal%20time%20to%20take%20time%20off%20%E2%80%94%20for%20planned%20or%20unexpected%20events.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20June%202020%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.abetterbalance.org%2Fmisled-misinformed%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20worker%20advocacy%20group%20A%20Better%20Balance%20found%20that%20an%20estimated%2018%20million%20workers%20across%2066%20United%20States%20employers%20were%20impacted%20by%20points-based%20or%20so-called%20%26quot%3Bno%20fault%26quot%3B%20attendance%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20companies%2C%20including%20mid-size%20ones%2C%20have%20started%20to%20implement%20a%20points-based%20system%20to%20track%20lateness%20and%20absences%2C%20Zambrano%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20problem%20is%2C%20he%20said%2C%20that%20the%20heavily%20automated%20points-based%20attendance%20systems%20used%20by%20companies%20like%20Walmart%20and%20Amazon%20%26quot%3Bmake%20a%20lot%20of%20mistakes%26quot%3B%20and%20seemingly%20have%20issues%20filtering%20%26quot%3Ban%20absence%20that%20is%20'unexcused'%20or%20an%20absence%20that%20is%20protected%26quot%3B%20by%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20stuff%20is%20happening%20very%20routinely%2C%20and%20people%20are%20just%20being%20laid%20off%20just%20because%20they%20hit%20these%20points%20and%20there's%20no%20one%20fixing%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Zambrano.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20absolutely%20crazy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20Amazon%20and%20Walmart%2C%20Yasman%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThese%20policies%20were%20created%20and%20are%20applied%20at%20a%20national%20level%2C%20so%20they%20do%20not%2C%20on%20their%20face%2C%20incorporate%2C%20reference%2C%20or%20consider%20more%20restrictive%20state%20laws%2C%20most%20notably%20in%20California%20and%20New%20York.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20law%20firm%20has%20been%20getting%20a%20surge%20of%20calls%20from%20fired%20workers%20with%20similar%20allegations%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Zambrano%2C%20West%20Coast%20Trial%20Lawyers%20has%20been%20regularly%20getting%20multiple%20calls%20a%20week%20from%20people%20reporting%20they%20were%20wrongly%20fired%20from%20their%20jobs%20after%20racking%20up%20too%20many%20points%20for%20absences%2C%20even%20though%20they%20claim%20their%20leave%20should%20have%20been%20protected%20or%20was%20already%20cleared%20with%20managers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20been%20a%20surge%20in%20the%20last%2018%20months%20of%20these%20types%20of%20calls%20coming%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20Zambrano%20said%2C%20noting%20that%20many%20calls%20are%20from%20people%20who%20say%20they're%20former%20Amazon%20or%20Walmart%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHalf%20of%20them%20say%20that%20the%20HR%20department%20or%20the%20direct%20supervisors%20will%20tell%20them%2C%20'We%20messed%20up%2C%20you%20should%20not%20have%20been%20fired%2C%20we%20will%20fix%20this%2C'%20and%20they%20don't%20fix%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Zambrano%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYasman%2C%20who%20is%20currently%20litigating%20three%20of%20these%20types%20of%20cases%20against%20Walmart%2C%20and%20two%20cases%20against%20Amazon%20explained%20that%20the%20%26quot%3Bcommon%20theme%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20lawsuits%20are%20that%20managers%20%26quot%3Beither%20approved%20or%20were%20aware%20of%20my%20clients'%20leaves%2Faccommodations%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bjust%20failed%20to%20properly%20input%20the%20data%20into%20the%20automated%20system%2C%20so%20the%20automated%20system%20terminated%20my%20clients%20once%20they%20hit%20the%20'five-point'%20mark.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20disputed%20the%20description%20of%20its%20points-based%20attendance%20system%20as%20totally%20%26quot%3Bautomated.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20attendance%20system%20works%20very%20similar%20to%20a%20standard%20time%20clock%20system%2C%26quot%3B%20Stephenson%2C%20Amazon's%20spokesperson%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BTo%20say%20there%20is%20total%20automation%20to%20the%20system%20is%20simply%20inaccurate.%20There%20are%20humans%20behind%20every%20system%2C%20and%20if%20employees%20have%20questions%20they%20have%20access%20to%20onsite%20HR%20managers%20or%20they%20get%20in%20contact%20with%20HR%26quot%3B%20via%20a%20company%20app.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EOne%20lawsuit%20against%20Amazon%20alleges%20a%20worker%20was%20fired%20after%20taking%20medical%20leave%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFormer%20Amazon%20ship%20dock%20worker%20Patricia%20Caputo%20was%20fired%20from%20the%20e-commerce%20behemoth%20in%20December%202022%20after%20she%20needed%20an%20emergency%20colonoscopy%20and%20took%20a%20short%20medical%20leave%2C%20according%20to%20one%20of%20the%20lawsuits%20filed%20against%20Amazon%20by%20West%20Coast%20Trial%20Lawyers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20just%20happened%20%E2%80%94%20no%20warning%2C%20no%20nothing.%20I%20just%20got%20a%20phone%20call%2C%20'You're%20fired%2C'%20from%20some%20random%20person%20at%20Amazon.%20I%20couldn't%20believe%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Caputo%2C%2052%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20a%20recent%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECaputo%2C%20who%20said%20in%20the%20lawsuit%20she%20suffers%20from%20a%20physical%20disability%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20her%20medical%20leave%20was%20previously%20approved%20by%20her%20manager%2C%20but%20apparently%20was%20not%20correctly%20input%20into%20the%20company's%20internal%20system%2C%20resulting%20in%20her%20termination.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Amazon%20logo%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65244e586561dd877e751144%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221392%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAmazon%20is%20being%20sued%20by%20workers%20who%20allege%20their%20employment%20rights%20were%20violated.%20%3Cp%3EArtur%20Widak%2FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20lawsuit%20filed%20last%20August%20in%20California's%20Kern%20County%20Superior%20Court%2C%20Caputo%20initially%20requested%20four%20days%20off%20from%20work%20to%20recover%20from%20the%20procedure%2C%20and%20she%20planned%20to%20return%20on%20December%2011%2C%202022.%20Caputo's%20doctor%20advised%20she%20take%20an%20extended%20medical%20leave%20through%20December%2013%20shortly%20after%20the%20procedure%20was%20done%20on%20December%208%2C%20the%20lawsuit%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20day%20of%20the%20procedure%2C%20Caputo%20notified%20Amazon's%20employee%20resource%20center%2C%20and%20she%20was%20told%20by%20a%20representative%20that%20her%20medical%20leave%20extension%20was%20approved%2C%20according%20to%20the%20lawsuit.%20However%2C%20the%20next%20day%2C%20Amazon%20called%20Caputo%20and%20%26quot%3Binformed%20her%20that%20her%20employment%26quot%3B%20with%20the%20company%20%26quot%3Bwas%20terminated%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20lawsuit%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECaputo%20wasn't%20given%20a%20reason%20for%20her%20firing%20and%20later%20that%20day%20received%20a%20direct%20deposit%20for%20her%20final%20paycheck%20from%20Amazon%2C%20according%20to%20the%20lawsuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20terrible.%20It%20was%20devastating%20to%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20Caputo%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThere%20was%20no%20one%20I%20could%20turn%20to%20or%20talk%20to%20about%20it.%20They%20immediately%20cut%20my%20mobile%20app%20off%20from%20me%20having%20access%20to%20it%2C%20so%20I%20couldn't%20even%20check%20back%20with%20anything%20that%20was%20going%20on.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20cut%20me%20off%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Caputo.%20%26quot%3BThere%20was%20no%20one%20I%20could%20talk%20to%20about%20their%20mistake.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%20says%20Caputo%20believes%20she%20was%20fired%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20of%20her%20physical%20disability%20and%20for%20seeking%20the%20reasonable%20accommodation%20of%20taking%20medically%20recommended%20days-off%20of%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20another%20lawsuit%20filed%20against%20Amazon%2C%20former%20warehouse%20associate%20Mekaliah%20Torres%20says%20she%20was%20hired%20in%20June%202023%20and%20disclosed%20she%20was%20pregnant%20during%20her%20registration.%20Torres%20was%20told%20to%20make%20a%20request%20for%20accommodations%20prior%20to%20her%20first%20day%20of%20work%2C%20the%20lawsuit%2C%20filed%20in%20California's%20Fresno%20County%20Superior%20Court%2C%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETorres%20told%20the%20company%20she%20would%20not%20be%20able%20to%20lift%20more%20than%2020%20pounds%2C%20but%20when%20she%20began%20working%20at%20Amazon%20the%20next%20month%2C%20she%20had%20to%20lift%20objects%20weighing%20up%20to%2080%20pounds%2C%20according%20to%20the%20lawsuit.%20Torres%20informed%20her%20manager%20that%20her%20pregnancy-related%20restrictions%20were%20being%20violated%20after%20about%20four%20hours%20of%20work%2C%20the%20lawsuit%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20manager%20told%20her%20if%20she%20did%20not%20feel%20safe%2C%20she%20could%20go%20home%2C%20so%20she%20did%2C%20according%20to%20the%20lawsuit.%20The%20lawsuit%20alleges%20that%20after%20more%20than%20two%20weeks%20of%20back-and-forth%20about%20her%20pregnancy%20accommodations%2C%20Torres%20received%20a%20termination%20letter%20falsely%20citing%20%26quot%3Bvoluntary%20resignation%20due%20to%20job%20abandonment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDefendant's%20adverse%20actions%2C%20including%2C%20but%20not%20limited%20to%2C%20Plaintiff's%20termination%2C%20and%20failure%20to%20accommodate%2C%20were%20at%20least%20in%20part%2C%20in%20retaliation%20for%20Plaintiff%20informing%20Defendant%20that%20she%20was%20pregnant%2C%20and%20due%20to%20her%20pregnancy-related%20restrictions%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20lawsuit%20alleges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20of%20the%20lawsuits%20filed%20against%20Walmart%2C%20former%20employee%20David%20Wagner%20said%20he%20was%20told%20he%20was%20fired%20in%20July%202022%20due%20to%20attendance%20issues%20because%20he%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bno%20show%26quot%3B%20when%20he%20had%20COVID-19.%20The%20lawsuit%2C%20filed%20in%20California's%20Riverside%20County%20Superior%20Court%2C%20alleges%20that%20on%20the%20day%20Wagner%2C%20a%20former%20front-end%20host%2C%20tested%20positive%2C%20he%20continuously%20called%20Walmart%20to%20inform%20the%20retail%20giant%20of%20his%20condition%20but%20got%20no%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Wagner%20reached%20out%20to%20a%20coworker%20about%20it%2C%20he%20was%20told%20he%20had%20two%20paid%20weeks%20off%20to%20recover%2C%20according%20to%20the%20lawsuit%2C%20which%20says%20Wagner%20called%20in%20almost%20every%20day%20to%20speak%20with%20someone%20at%20Walmart%20regarding%20his%20condition%20and%20return%20to%20work%20date.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%20says%20Wagner%20never%20received%20pay%20for%20the%20days%20he%20was%20out%20sick%20and%20when%20he%20finally%20returned%20to%20work%20on%20July%2021%2C%20he%20was%20informed%20he%20had%20been%20terminated%20days%20earlier%20on%20July%2015.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20another%20lawsuit%20filed%20against%20Walmart%20earlier%20last%20month%20in%20California's%20Sacramento%20County%20Superior%20Court%2C%20former%20employee%20Larreon%20Murphy%20said%20he%20was%20fired%20in%20November%202023%20for%20%26quot%3Bexcessive%20absences%26quot%3B%20after%20he%20got%20COVID-19%20and%20needed%20time%20off%20and%20after%20he%20received%20clearance%20by%20a%20manager%20to%20come%20in%20for%20his%20shift%20late%20on%20multiple%20dates%20so%20he%20could%20pick%20up%20his%20children%20from%20after-school%20programs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMurphy%2C%20according%20to%20the%20lawsuit%2C%20believes%20he%20was%20terminated%20%26quot%3Bin%20retaliation%20for%20his%20positive%20COVID-19%20test%20result%20and%20subsequent%20need%20for%20a%20short%20medical%20leave.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Walmart%20manager%20later%20admitted%20in%20a%20recorded%20phone%20call%20to%20Murphy%20that%20he%20was%20%26quot%3Bwrongfully%20terminated%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20lawsuit%20says.%20Murphy%20was%20then%20offered%20a%20%26quot%3Breinstatement%26quot%3B%20of%20his%20job%20on%20a%20different%20shift%2C%20but%20Murphy%20explained%20the%20new%20shift%20conflicted%20with%20another%20job%20he%20had%2C%20according%20to%20the%20lawsuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%20says%20the%20manager%20emailed%20Murphy%20%26quot%3Bin%20a%20bad%20faith%20attempt%20to%20reinstate%26quot%3B%20his%20employment%20%26quot%3Bwithout%20his%20consent%20or%20approval%2C%26quot%3B%20prompting%20Murphy%20to%20respond%20that%20he%20never%20agreed%20to%20return%20to%20Walmart.%20A%20December%202023%20separation%20letter%20stated%20Murphy%20was%20reinstated%20and%20that%20he%20later%20submitted%20a%20resignation%2C%20according%20to%20the%20lawsuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPlaintiff%20is%20informed%20and%20believes%20Walmart%20has%20adopted%20a%20national%20policy%20regarding%20handling%20wrongful%20terminations%20associated%20with%20disability%20leaves%20that%20formally%20calls%20for%20fraudulent%20reinstatement%20of%20all%20employees%20who%20have%20been%20unlawfully%20terminated%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20lawsuit%20alleges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EYasman%20thinks%20policies%20were%20designed%20'to%20keep%20your%20sick%2C%20disabled%2C%20pregnant%20people%20out%20of%20work'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYasman%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20it's%20his%20law%20firm's%20goal%20to%20win%20punitive%20damages%20in%20these%20cases%20at%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20confident%20the%20'point%20systems'%20were%20created%20with%20malicious%20and%20oppressive%20intent%2C%26quot%3B%20Yasman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Yasman%2C%20the%20lawsuits%20filed%20by%20West%20Coast%20Trial%20Lawyers%20against%20Walmart%20and%20Amazon%20do%20not%20specifically%20mention%20the%20points-based%20attendance%20systems%20even%20though%20five%20of%20the%20suits%20stem%20from%20these%20policies%20because%20he%20says%20they're%20typically%20part%20of%20the%20companies'%20defense%20to%20their%20lawsuits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTheir%20general%20position%20is%20that%20a%20policy%20that%20applies%20universally%20and%20equally%20to%20all%20employees%20cannot%20possibly%20discriminate%20against%20anyone%2C%26quot%3B%20Yasman%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20attorney%20said%20he%20believes%20that%20the%20%26quot%3Balmost%20total%20automation%20of%20both%20companies'%20human%20resources%20dealings%20is%20extremely%20nefarious.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBecause%20by%20most%20metrics%20they're%20the%20world's%20two%20biggest%20companies%2C%26quot%3B%20Yasman%20said%20of%20Amazon%20and%20Walmart%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20the%20size%20and%20influence%20of%20the%20two%20companies%20will%20likely%20set%20a%20precedent%20and%20predict%20trends%20for%20the%20future%20of%20HR%20operations%20of%20all%20businesses.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYasman%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20do%20suspect%20the%20policies%20were%20designed%20in%20order%20to%20keep%20your%20sick%2C%20disabled%2C%20pregnant%20people%20out%20of%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMillions%20of%20workers%20are%20impacted%20by%20similar%20attendance%20policies%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%202020%20report%20by%20A%20Better%20Balance%20found%20that%20millions%20of%20workers%20in%20the%20US%20were%20impacted%20by%20points-based%20or%20%26quot%3Bno%20fault%26quot%3B%20attendance%20policies%20at%2066%20companies%20that%20included%20a%20slew%20of%20major%20ones.%20Walmart%20was%20among%20those%2066%20companies%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B'No%20fault'%26quot%3B%20attendance%20policies%2C%20as%20they%20are%20often%20called%2C%20are%20used%20by%20some%20of%20the%20nation's%20largest%20companies%2C%26quot%3B%20the%202020%20report%20read%2C%20%26quot%3Bto%20encourage%20workers%20to%20show%20up%20for%20their%20shifts%20and%20penalize%20them%20when%20they%20do%20not.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYet%20too%20frequently%2C%20these%20attendance%20policies%20are%20used%20to%20infringe%20on%20workers'%20rights%20by%20punishing%20them%20with%20'points'%20or%20'occurrences'%20for%20absences%20that%20are%20legally%20protected%2C%20including%20time%20off%20for%20serious%20medical%20needs%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EElizabeth%20Gedmark%2C%20an%20attorney%20and%20vice%20president%20of%20the%20nonprofit%20legal%20advocacy%20organization%20behind%20the%20report%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20A%20Better%20Balance%20has%20heard%20about%20problems%20surrounding%20companies'%20use%20of%20points-based%20attendance%20systems%20for%20many%20years%20and%20that%20the%20group%20has%20been%20fighting%20back%20against%20the%20%26quot%3Babusive%26quot%3B%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGedmark%20called%20these%20types%20of%20systems%20%26quot%3Ba%20growing%20trend%26quot%3B%20as%20more%20and%20more%20companies%20turn%20to%20them%2C%20which%20she%20views%20as%20worrisome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20concerns%20that%20it%20is%20a%20growing%20trend%2C%20especially%20because%20of%20the%20increased%20use%20of%20technology%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Gedmark.%20%26quot%3BThe%20issue%20is%20that%20if%20a%20company%20is%20not%20paying%20attention%20to%20how%20their%20automatic%20system%20is%20working%20or%20their%20policies%20%E2%80%94%20and%20often%20it%20can%20even%20be%20intentional%20%E2%80%94%20then%20they%20may%20give%20someone%20points%20or%20a%20demerit%20basically%20for%20a%20lawfully%20protected%20absence.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20see%20these%20types%20of%20policies%20in%20some%20of%20the%20country's%20biggest%20employers%2C%20you%20just%20have%20to%20pay%20attention%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20these%20employers%20are%20employing%20low-wage%20workers%20or%20workers%20who%20are%20in%20vulnerable%20positions%20and%20may%20not%20have%20the%20bargaining%20power%20to%20ask%20for%20their%20rights%2C%26quot%3B%20Gedmark%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalmart-amazon-lawsuits-employee-attendance-tracking-points-system-policy-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708509601000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cfde8ba610a9069d5a33d5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalmart-amazon-lawsuits-employee-attendance-tracking-points-system-policy-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Walmart%20and%20Amazon%20are%20facing%20wrongful%20termination%20lawsuits%20stemming%20from%20the%20mega-companies'%20points-based%20attendance%20policies%2C%20according%20to%20attorneys.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22nmusumeci%40businessinsider.com%20(Natalie%20Musumeci)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalmart-amazon-lawsuits-employee-attendance-tracking-points-system-policy-2024-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ranveer%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20Shaktimaan%20to%20not%20be%20a%20trilogy%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1