th%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20been%20estimated%20that%20UNRWA%2C%20which%20does%20not%20have%20a%20strategic%20reserve%20for%20emergencies%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Funrwa-asks-for-eu-funds-to-maintain-lifesaving-aid-delivery%2Fa-68219361%5C%22%3Emight%20start%20to%20feel%20the%20impact%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20funding%20shortages%20at%C2%A0the%20end%20of%20March.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20will%20be%20a%20kind%20of%20hierarchy%20as%20to%20how%20drastic%20%5BUNRWA%E2%80%99s%5D%20collapse%20might%20be%20in%20terms%20of%20consequences%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Jorgen%C2%A0Jensehaugen%2C%20a%20senior%20researcher%20at%20Norway%E2%80%99s%20Peace%20Research%20Institute%20Oslo.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20would%20be%20Gaza%20first%2C%20then%20Lebanon%20and%20Syria%20second%2C%20then%20the%20West%20Bank%20and%20then%20Jordan.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20impact%20will%20be%20most%20keenly%20felt%20in%20Lebanon%2C%20which%20is%20already%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Feconomic-crisis-is-egypt-the-new-lebanon%2Fa-64469810%5C%22%3Eon%20an%20economic%20precipice%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%E2%80%9D%20confirmed%20Joost%20Hiltermann%2C%20head%20of%20the%20Middle%20East%20and%20North%20Africa%20program%C2%A0at%20the%20International%20Crisis%20Group.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Lebanese%20state%20lacks%20the%20capacity%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20additional%20burden%20of%20caring%20for%20Palestinian%20refugees.%20The%20same%20is%20true%20for%20Syria.%20By%20comparison%2C%20Jordan%20does%20have%20that%20capacity.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Lebanon%2C%20infrastructure%20in%20long-standing%20Palestinian%20refugee%20camps%2C%C2%A0which%20the%20Lebanese%20state%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Flebanon-six-killed-in-clashes-in-palestinian-refugee-camp%2Fa-66804967%5C%22%3Etends%20not%20to%20have%20much%20control%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20anyway%2C%C2%A0would%20just%20collapse%2C%20Jensehaugen%20told%3Cem%3E%20DW%3C%2Fem%3E