20title%3D%5C%22External%20link%20%E2%80%94%20a%202022%20study%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%202022%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20topic%20of%20UNRWA%E2%80%99s%20funding%20struggles%2C%C2%A0the%20agency%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fpalestinian-refugees-unrwa-collapse-us-aid%2Fa-55660557%5C%22%3Elong%20run%20a%20deficit%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they%20found%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20so-called%20stability%20argument%E2%80%9D%20to%20have%20been%20a%20key%20motivator%20for%20donor%20contributions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20other%20words%2C%20funding%20UNRWA%20is%20a%20cheap%20way%20of%20securing%20stability%20in%20the%20region%20because%20it%20means%20that%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20children%20get%20educated%2C%E2%80%9D%20Jensehaugen%20explained%2C%20noting%20that%20poverty%20and%20lack%20of%20education%20are%20proven%20drivers%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fiiss-military-think-tank-says-more-dangerous-decade-likely%2Fa-68243699%5C%22%3Eextremism%20and%20crime%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSo%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20really%20huge%20paradox%20now%20with%20constraining%20funding%20for%20UNRWA%2C%E2%80%9D%20Jensehaugen%20continued.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20potential%20for%20instability%20is%20so%20clear%20and%20donors%20already%20know%20it%20can%20get%20worse.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20observers%20say%20that%20European%20governments%20are%20well%20aware%20that%20if%20UNRWA%20fails%2C%20they%20could%20see%20a%20new%20wave%20of%20irregular%20migration%20from%20Lebanon%20and%20Jordan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CUNRWA%E2%80%99s%20collapse%20would%20be%20dangerous%20for%20local%20stability%20in%20each%20location%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20Crisis%20Group%E2%80%99s%20Hiltermann%20confirms.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20if%20it%20links%20up%20with%20an%20ongoing%20war%20in%20Gaza%2C%20or%20even%20the%20mass%20expulsion%20of%20Palestinians%20from%20Gaza%20into%20Egypt%2C%C2%A0which%20would%20prompt%20an%20escal